      • isAutoRetrieveGeneratedKeys

        public boolean isAutoRetrieveGeneratedKeys()
        When this returns true, the proxy logic always call Statement.getGeneratedKeys() and set it to ExecutionInfo. Also, if Statement.getGeneratedKeys() is called, it will return cached generated keys ResultSet when cached ResultSet is still open. If cached ResultSet is closed, calling Statement.getGeneratedKeys() returns a new ResultSet. (Calling Statement.getGeneratedKeys() multiple times is not defined in JDBC spec. Therefore, behavior depends on JDBC driver.) If false is returned, ExecutionInfo.getGeneratedKeys() returns null.
        Returns:
        true if generated-keys retrieval is enabled
        Since:
        1.4.5

      • isGeneratedKeysProxyEnabled

        public boolean isGeneratedKeysProxyEnabled()
        When JdbcProxyFactory for generated-keys is specified, return true.
        Returns:
        true when ResultSetProxyLogicFactory for generated keys is specified
        Since:
        1.4.5
        See Also:
        ProxyConfig.Builder.generatedKeysProxyLogicFactory(ResultSetProxyLogicFactory)

      • isAutoCloseGeneratedKeys

        public boolean isAutoCloseGeneratedKeys()
        Whether to auto close ResultSet for generated-keys that is automatically retrieved. When this returns true, always close the ResultSet for generated keys when QueryExecutionListener.afterQuery(ExecutionInfo, List) has finished. The result of Statement.getGeneratedKeys() method will not be closed by this. Only auto retrieved ResultSet of generated keys is closed.
        Since:
        1.4.5

      • isRetrieveGeneratedKeysForBatchStatement

        public boolean isRetrieveGeneratedKeysForBatchStatement()
        Perform generated-keys auto retrieval for batch statement. Default is set to false.
        Since:
        1.4.6

      • isRetrieveGeneratedKeysForBatchPreparedOrCallable

        public boolean isRetrieveGeneratedKeysForBatchPreparedOrCallable()
